1
00:01:32,308 --> 00:01:32,948
Of course.

2
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:36,029
I remember now.

3
00:01:38,090 --> 00:01:39,150
It was Frieren.

4
00:01:41,471 --> 00:01:46,272
The mage who made great contributions
to humanity's analysis of Solltrag.

5
00:01:47,272 --> 00:01:50,893
And sent more demons to the
grave than anyone else in history.

6
00:01:54,394 --> 00:01:56,195
Frieren the Slayer.

7
00:01:58,435 --> 00:02:00,916
One of the geniuses I despise.

8
00:02:12,927 --> 00:02:15,009
It's important that you
rest for the time being.

9
00:02:15,549 --> 00:02:16,410
I appreciate it.

10
00:02:24,737 --> 00:02:25,438
Whoa there!

11
00:02:27,119 --> 00:02:27,860
You doing okay?

12
00:02:29,882 --> 00:02:32,103
I will survive, but only
because of you two.

13
00:02:32,864 --> 00:02:33,445
I'm grateful.

14
00:02:39,185 --> 00:02:41,526
I'll pardon your companion
for her actions as well.

15
00:02:42,427 --> 00:02:44,448
She was right to take
a stand when she did.

16
00:02:46,329 --> 00:02:48,690
Which means nothing's
stopping Frieren from coming back.

17
00:02:49,510 --> 00:02:51,091
The peace envoy's
as good as dead.

18
00:02:52,352 --> 00:02:55,853
Also, please know that Mistress
Frieren didn't kill your guard.

19
00:02:57,034 --> 00:02:57,654
I am aware.

20
00:02:58,174 --> 00:02:59,995
The demons are to
blame for that, too.

21
00:03:00,836 --> 00:03:04,277
More importantly, you said
this woman's name is Frieren?

22
00:03:04,738 --> 00:03:04,978
Yes.

23
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:09,646
which almost certainly makes her the
elven mage who adventured with the hero.

24
00:03:10,886 --> 00:03:12,887
I've committed a grave
discourtesy against her.

25
00:03:14,727 --> 00:03:17,448
My family owes a debt to
that great band of heroes.

26
00:03:18,188 --> 00:03:21,489
During my grandfather's rule,
this town was attacked by demons.

27
00:03:22,069 --> 00:03:25,350
Frieren and her comrades drove
them off and saved our people.

28
00:03:26,091 --> 00:03:27,731
That same enemy has returned.

29
00:03:28,371 --> 00:03:30,972
Aura, one of the Seven
Sages of Destruction.

30
00:03:33,914 --> 00:03:35,795
It's been a while, Aura.

31
00:03:36,795 --> 00:03:37,635
Eighty years.

32
00:03:38,135 --> 00:03:41,016
The decades fly by,
don't they, Frieren?

33
00:03:44,877 --> 00:03:46,978
No doubt you planned
to attack the town ahead.

34
00:03:48,379 --> 00:03:50,579
But I'd appreciate it if
you turned back now.

35
00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:52,380
That won't do.

36
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:53,960
Why not?

37
00:04:14,819 --> 00:04:17,901
Because I carry an advantage
that assures my success.

38
00:04:19,443 --> 00:04:19,603
Oh?

39
00:04:23,886 --> 00:04:25,587
You have more
puppets than before.

40
00:04:26,608 --> 00:04:31,191
Your magic must be unbelievably powerful if
you're able to control this many at once.

41
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:35,895
I'm sure no human could even
begin to dream of wielding such might.

42
00:04:37,676 --> 00:04:40,318
But this dark magic is
enough to make me vomit.

43
00:04:40,979 --> 00:04:41,900
It's disgusting.

44
00:04:42,813 --> 00:04:44,554
Vomit? you wound me.

45
00:04:44,894 --> 00:04:47,195
It took a lot of work to
gather such an army.

46
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,480
I recognize some
of those crests.

47
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:08,305
Right then, it seems my best
option is to kill you once and for all.

48
00:05:08,845 --> 00:05:10,366
The scales of obedience.

49
00:05:11,944 --> 00:05:14,925
They're why we haven't been
able to defeat Aura over the years.

50
00:05:16,646 --> 00:05:21,648
Her magic allows her to control a person's
will, forces them to obey her every command.

51
00:05:23,868 --> 00:05:27,750
The Seven Sages of Destruction wield
power beyond human comprehension.

52
00:05:28,990 --> 00:05:35,212
We believe Aura places her soul and the soul of her
target on the scales, then weighs them against each other.

53
00:05:36,713 --> 00:05:39,434
Whoever has greater mana
gains control of the other.

54
00:05:40,372 --> 00:05:42,674
turning them into a
puppet for all eternity.

55
00:05:44,135 --> 00:05:48,038
Until their body withers
away and only armor remains.

56
00:05:48,058 --> 00:05:52,122
The risk involved
makes the spell powerful.

57
00:05:53,243 --> 00:05:57,506
And when it's cast by someone as
mighty as Aura, it cannot be overcome.

58
00:05:58,787 --> 00:06:00,929
There must be a means
of countering the spell.

59
00:06:03,291 --> 00:06:08,956
Aura's strength seems unbeatable, but the
scales themselves are fair and partial judges.

60
00:06:10,382 --> 00:06:15,803
If a soul with greater mana than Aura's were
to be placed upon them, she could be defeated.

61
00:06:18,584 --> 00:06:27,106
Still, according to what we know, that has yet to happen once in
the last 500 years, ever since she became a Sage of Destruction.

62
00:06:28,006 --> 00:06:30,907
You mean... there's no way
for us to stand against her?

63
00:06:35,748 --> 00:06:37,228
Once upon a time, there was.

64
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:43,362
Those with fierce determination were
able to temporarily resist Aura's spell.

65
00:06:46,143 --> 00:06:50,384
The warriors who had wills forged
of iron, the greatest among us.

66
00:06:51,444 --> 00:06:53,265
But even then it was temporary.

67
00:06:54,225 --> 00:06:56,286
Which made them
her primary targets.

68
00:06:56,886 --> 00:06:59,827
They stood in her way,
threatened her victory.

69
00:07:00,908 --> 00:07:01,348
And so...

70
00:07:03,873 --> 00:07:09,616
When she finally broke them, Aura the guillotine made
certain they would no longer pose a threat to her.

71
00:07:11,137 --> 00:07:12,097
It's a tragic tale.

72
00:07:19,301 --> 00:07:23,323
Well, haven't I impressed
you with my immortal soldiers?

73
00:07:38,408 --> 00:07:39,749
My, this is a surprise.

74
00:07:40,669 --> 00:07:43,210
You dispelled the magic
I used to control them.

75
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,971
No one's ever done that before.

76
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:53,053
Such a formidable act must consume a monumental
amount of mana, though, leaving you exhausted.

77
00:07:54,133 --> 00:07:56,594
Why would you use such
a roundabout method?

78
00:07:58,555 --> 00:08:02,256
The last time you faced me, you
were casting flashy spells left and right.

79
00:08:02,276 --> 00:08:06,798
Himmel scolded
me after that battle.

80
00:08:08,753 --> 00:08:09,954
You're holding back for him.

81
00:08:10,434 --> 00:08:12,576
I don't see why his words
should matter to you.

82
00:08:14,217 --> 00:08:14,897
Why wouldn't they?

83
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,819
Because Himmel is
rotting in the ground.

84
00:08:20,201 --> 00:08:21,382
Thank you for saying that.

85
00:08:24,204 --> 00:08:29,168
You've reminded me that demons are just
monsters, so I can kill you without mercy.

86
00:08:30,188 --> 00:08:30,709
All right.

87
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:33,751
I've regained
most of my mobility.

88
00:08:35,731 --> 00:08:38,252
Father, this place
is safe, right?

89
00:08:38,912 --> 00:08:39,152
Yes.

90
00:08:40,152 --> 00:08:45,014
There's a defensive barrier around the church,
though it's not as powerful as the towns, I'm afraid.

91
00:08:46,194 --> 00:08:46,554
Got it.

92
00:08:47,195 --> 00:08:48,535
Graf, you wait here.

93
00:08:49,455 --> 00:08:50,295
Not so fast.

94
00:08:50,916 --> 00:08:52,416
What do you plan to do, brat?

95
00:08:53,356 --> 00:08:56,978
We may have escaped the demons, but
they're still out there plotting somewhere.

96
00:08:57,818 --> 00:09:00,038
Mr. Stark, be reasonable.

97
00:09:01,239 --> 00:09:04,480
We only injured that demon before
because we took him by surprise.

98
00:09:05,568 --> 00:09:07,929
Even with that advantage,
we couldn't finish him off.

99
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:13,732
If we had kept fighting those two, we
would have been the ones who were killed.

100
00:09:15,713 --> 00:09:17,674
Someone's gotta step
up and try to stop them.

101
00:09:20,555 --> 00:09:24,236
But... You're right.

102
00:09:25,337 --> 00:09:26,377
Let me do this with you.

103
00:09:28,959 --> 00:09:29,199
No.

104
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:31,820
You need to head
to the guard station.

105
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:34,141
Start evacuating the townsfolk.

106
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:36,612
You'll go out there alone?

107
00:09:39,774 --> 00:09:40,114
Yeah.

108
00:09:41,415 --> 00:09:42,055
No sweat!

109
00:09:43,175 --> 00:09:45,636
I'll swallow my pride
and beg Frieren to return!

110
00:09:51,239 --> 00:09:54,200
She's obviously the only person
around who can defeat Lügner!

111
00:09:55,581 --> 00:09:58,562
Not what I was expecting,
but more realistic.

112
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:03,552
Here.

113
00:10:04,313 --> 00:10:06,474
The guards will listen to you
if you show them this crest.

114
00:10:08,155 --> 00:10:08,695
Very well.

115
00:10:10,756 --> 00:10:11,677
I'm heading out of town.

116
00:10:14,419 --> 00:10:14,959
What is it?

117
00:10:15,779 --> 00:10:16,300
Your arm.

118
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:18,101
It's all covered in blood.

119
00:10:19,262 --> 00:10:21,203
You're not worried they'll
question you at the gate?

120
00:10:23,204 --> 00:10:23,844
I'll be fine.

121
00:10:24,725 --> 00:10:25,886
Comes with being a warrior.

122
00:10:26,686 --> 00:10:28,087
Plus, it's not that much.

123
00:10:28,952 --> 00:10:31,954
I've never seen a warrior walk
through town with two bloody hands.

124
00:10:32,314 --> 00:10:33,455
You look like a murderer.

125
00:10:34,415 --> 00:10:35,356
You're one to talk.

126
00:10:35,756 --> 00:10:37,237
You've got just as
much on you as I do.

127
00:10:39,958 --> 00:10:41,179
Wait, whose blood is this?

128
00:10:41,539 --> 00:10:42,359
Couldn't be mine.

129
00:10:42,379 --> 00:10:46,642
Hey!

130
00:10:47,662 --> 00:10:49,223
What is the matter with you?

131
00:10:53,185 --> 00:10:55,347
Mr. Stark, there's
mana in this blood.

132
00:10:57,388 --> 00:10:57,768
Fern!

133
00:11:06,992 --> 00:11:08,092
An axe?!

134
00:11:12,916 --> 00:11:16,616
Unbelievable, I've got to
be dreaming or something.

135
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:20,139
Because that looks like
my master’s technique.

136
00:11:23,563 --> 00:11:27,263
I meant to hit your vitals, but
you’re faster than I expected.

137
00:11:28,387 --> 00:11:31,237
It truly wasn’t my intention
to make you suffer.

138
00:11:35,761 --> 00:11:37,761
Why do you look so shocked?

139
00:11:38,285 --> 00:11:41,885
Did you think your attack could killed
me? That I was mortally wounded?

140
00:11:42,609 --> 00:11:43,636
 No.

141
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:46,161
You're surprised you didn't
sense us as we approached.

142
00:11:48,581 --> 00:11:51,422
You aren't unique in your
ability to conceal your presence.

143
00:11:52,082 --> 00:11:54,443
It's a simple matter of
controlling one's mana.

144
00:11:55,043 --> 00:11:57,284
Any demon can do the
same, should they wish.

145
00:11:58,924 --> 00:12:03,645
To be fair, it's hardly a noble way to
approach a battle between two mages.

146
00:12:04,085 --> 00:12:05,206
But these things happen.

147
00:12:06,766 --> 00:12:08,186
You like to hear yourself talk.

148
00:12:09,007 --> 00:12:10,387
Didn't you come here to kill me?

149
00:12:12,435 --> 00:12:16,096
True, but seeing as you're still alive,
I might as well ask a few questions.

150
00:12:18,697 --> 00:12:20,518
Unless, of course,
you're in a hurry to die.

151
00:12:22,899 --> 00:12:23,379
Go on.

152
00:12:26,860 --> 00:12:28,381
How strong is that boy?

153
00:12:29,921 --> 00:12:32,022
He's Eisen the
Warrior's best student.

154
00:12:32,962 --> 00:12:33,422
I see.

155
00:12:34,263 --> 00:12:35,063
How unfortunate.

156
00:12:36,343 --> 00:12:38,104
The poor thing will
die a torturous death.

157
00:12:38,864 --> 00:12:40,525
Linie likes to take her time.

158
00:12:43,728 --> 00:12:44,549
One last thing.

159
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:46,991
Where is Frieren hiding?

160
00:12:50,335 --> 00:12:52,037
She fled town after escaping.

161
00:12:53,278 --> 00:12:56,181
She had to, because you
killed the Dungeon Guard.

162
00:12:57,162 --> 00:12:59,084
Graf Granat blamed
me for that as well.

163
00:13:00,005 --> 00:13:01,927
Is it really such a
serious offense?

164
00:13:03,108 --> 00:13:04,109
The penalty's death.

165
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:09,563
Still, a woman like Frieren wouldn't
flee because of such a danger.

166
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:13,305
It's obvious she holds a
grudge against demons.

167
00:13:14,466 --> 00:13:18,409
One so spiteful she taught her
student a spell designed solely to kill us.

168
00:13:20,611 --> 00:13:22,412
No, she would not run away.

169
00:13:23,593 --> 00:13:25,154
She left for another reason.

170
00:13:28,637 --> 00:13:29,578
For Lady Aura.

171
00:13:33,841 --> 00:13:35,222
Do not take another step.

172
00:13:36,729 --> 00:13:38,910
I suspect you know
exactly where she's headed.

173
00:13:39,491 --> 00:13:40,011
Explain.

174
00:13:41,292 --> 00:13:42,552
You're wasting your time.

175
00:13:43,893 --> 00:13:46,755
You were lying when you said
your intent wasn't for me to suffer.

176
00:13:47,755 --> 00:13:49,536
That attack was
never meant to kill me.

177
00:13:50,237 --> 00:13:52,258
It was revenge for
catching you off guard.

178
00:13:53,458 --> 00:14:00,963
You are a proud and arrogant demon, so sure of your strength
that you see Mistress Frieren as the only threat in your way.

179
00:14:02,443 --> 00:14:05,085
Underestimating me has
put you in a dire predicament.

180
00:14:07,898 --> 00:14:11,260
From this distance, I can blast
a hole clean through your heart.

181
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:13,561
Try it.

182
00:14:14,601 --> 00:14:16,622
Your head will fly before
you get the chance.

183
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:29,308
Mistress Frieren, am I
of any real use to you?

184
00:14:30,128 --> 00:14:31,509
Why would you ask such a thing?

185
00:14:33,544 --> 00:14:35,545
I'm not as skilled
with magic as you are.

186
00:14:36,486 --> 00:14:37,846
That's more than apparent.

187
00:14:39,427 --> 00:14:41,908
I've lived many, many
more years than you have.

188
00:14:42,789 --> 00:14:44,249
You can't hope
to catch up to me.

189
00:14:47,271 --> 00:14:47,811
I see.

190
00:14:49,212 --> 00:14:52,714
Of course, that only applies to your
technique and your mana reserves.

191
00:14:53,994 --> 00:14:55,535
I often let you handle monsters.

192
00:14:55,835 --> 00:14:57,336
You prove yourself
in those battles.

193
00:14:57,836 --> 00:15:00,417
Yes, you force me
to fight them often.

194
00:15:00,778 --> 00:15:01,398
Apologies.

195
00:15:02,810 --> 00:15:05,130
Battles end sooner
whenever you fight by my side.

196
00:15:06,450 --> 00:15:08,932
You fire off spells
much faster than I do.

197
00:15:11,756 --> 00:15:12,456
Human.

198
00:15:13,550 --> 00:15:17,150
I've dedicated the majority of
my life to the pursuit of magic.

199
00:15:18,174 --> 00:15:19,274
As have I.

200
00:15:34,223 --> 00:15:36,025
How is she
responding so quickly?

201
00:15:37,266 --> 00:15:41,129
If I hadn't acted reflexively,
that would have pierced my heart.

202
00:15:42,230 --> 00:15:46,254
You blocked my attack, which must
mean your heart is your weak point.

203
00:15:47,635 --> 00:15:48,415
This girl...

204
00:15:50,377 --> 00:15:50,938
Interesting.

205
00:15:51,898 --> 00:15:54,501
You weren't lying about
dedicating your life to magic.

206
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:57,163
That's good.

207
00:15:57,463 --> 00:15:59,505
I won't need to hold
back in this fight.

208
00:16:00,446 --> 00:16:01,227
Varterie!

209
00:16:04,905 --> 00:16:06,505
It sounds like
they've gotten started.

210
00:16:08,546 --> 00:16:10,126
That makes me
a little bit jealous.

211
00:16:10,986 --> 00:16:12,326
Our fight is all but over.

212
00:16:14,287 --> 00:16:17,167
Perhaps I'll observe
their battle from afar.

213
00:16:18,287 --> 00:16:20,548
Lord Lügner gets
cross when I interfere.

214
00:16:26,009 --> 00:16:26,469
You're up?

215
00:16:27,229 --> 00:16:29,229
We're not finished yet!

216
00:16:29,429 --> 00:16:32,110
Aren't you tough.

217
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:34,090
Perhaps this will be amusing.

218
00:16:38,335 --> 00:16:42,875
My mana, technique, and
control are all far superior to hers.

219
00:17:03,755 --> 00:17:05,916
She can't compare
to me in any way.

220
00:17:06,416 --> 00:17:08,217
The very thought
of it is ridiculous.

221
00:17:09,537 --> 00:17:12,078
However, she is fast.

222
00:17:13,559 --> 00:17:22,042
I'm being overwhelmed by
the sheer number of her attacks.

223
00:17:22,943 --> 00:17:24,143
Damn you, Frieren.

224
00:17:24,924 --> 00:17:27,425
How did you train this
girl to put up such a fight?

225
00:17:31,865 --> 00:17:32,665
It's no matter.

226
00:17:33,306 --> 00:17:35,487
She'll exhaust her mana soon.

227
00:17:48,507 --> 00:17:52,195
On second thought, I'm
not sure I can wait her out.

228
00:17:53,715 --> 00:17:59,158
If I can just create an opening...
Linie, quit playing around!

229
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:00,959
Hurry up and kill that boy!

230
00:18:08,234 --> 00:18:10,075
The human wants
to deny me my fun.

231
00:18:10,536 --> 00:18:13,162
He's refusing to do
anything but defend himself.

232
00:18:32,252 --> 00:18:34,554
I don't understand
the way you're fighting.

233
00:18:35,335 --> 00:18:36,976
Your technique
is like my master's.

234
00:18:38,212 --> 00:18:40,837
I'm exceptional at reading
the mana in other people.

235
00:18:42,220 --> 00:18:49,294
My specialty is memorizing the way it flows inside of a person
as they move, which allows me to imitate them, just like this.

236
00:19:14,282 --> 00:19:17,703
I recognized your technique the
moment you attacked us at the mansion.

237
00:19:18,703 --> 00:19:26,345
Because I memorized it years ago,
as I watched a great warrior fight.

238
00:19:27,185 --> 00:19:28,885
What an odd coincidence.

239
00:19:28,905 --> 00:19:31,066
Fate is a funny thing.

240
00:19:35,417 --> 00:19:36,898
You mean...

241
00:19:36,998 --> 00:19:40,219
I'm going to take your life using
Eisen the Warrior's movements.

242
00:19:41,839 --> 00:19:44,580
If I am dreaming,
then this is a nightmare.

243
00:19:47,501 --> 00:19:52,523
I can't win against her.

244
00:19:58,425 --> 00:19:59,826
There, he's finally fallen.

245
00:20:00,606 --> 00:20:01,386
I should go back.

246
00:20:02,346 --> 00:20:04,087
I don't want to
upset Lord Lügner.

247
00:20:08,008 --> 00:20:08,669
Is that it?

248
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:11,812
Is this how it ends?

249
00:20:16,416 --> 00:20:17,777
Stand up, Stark.

250
00:20:18,157 --> 00:20:19,379
Find the strength.

251
00:20:19,719 --> 00:20:22,561
No matter how battered
you get, you cannot fall.

252
00:20:23,722 --> 00:20:26,225
Why do we keep
sparring like this?

253
00:20:27,306 --> 00:20:29,768
No matter how hard I try,
I'm not going to beat you.

254
00:20:30,869 --> 00:20:31,770
Of course not.

255
00:20:32,170 --> 00:20:34,032
I'm far stronger than you are.

256
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:36,461
Then what's the point?

257
00:20:37,261 --> 00:20:37,862
Look at you.

258
00:20:38,182 --> 00:20:39,964
You're back on
your feet, aren't you?

259
00:20:40,724 --> 00:20:42,126
You haven't lost yet.

260
00:20:43,707 --> 00:20:44,808
That makes no sense.

261
00:20:45,969 --> 00:20:46,870
Listen, Stark.

262
00:20:47,590 --> 00:20:50,553
I'll teach you the secret to
defeating powerful opponents.

263
00:20:51,894 --> 00:20:52,514
It's simple.

264
00:20:53,335 --> 00:20:56,238
All you have to do is keep getting
back up and hitting your enemy.

265
00:20:56,938 --> 00:20:57,639
Understand?

266
00:20:58,620 --> 00:21:02,283
The winner is the warrior
who's still on their feet at the end.

267
00:21:06,374 --> 00:21:08,576
You talked like it
was so easy, Master.

268
00:21:09,676 --> 00:21:11,238
You and your crazy logic.

269
00:21:12,458 --> 00:21:14,740
You should have trained your
brain as much as your body.

270
00:21:17,062 --> 00:21:19,303
A smarter person would
have stayed in the dirt.

271
00:21:19,924 --> 00:21:21,245
I've already defeated you.

272
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:24,227
Yet here I am, still standing.

273
00:21:26,509 --> 00:21:30,952
You know, now that I think about it, my
master's blows were heavier than yours.

274
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:35,115
You're just the poor
imitation of a great warrior.

275
00:21:40,980 --> 00:21:45,684
Imitation or not, I'll
still be the death of you.

276
00:21:45,784 --> 00:21:47,325
Erfassen.

277
00:21:47,365 --> 00:21:48,046
Vertarie!

278
00:22:01,282 --> 00:22:04,424
Wideswing, with no
regard for defense.

279
00:22:04,984 --> 00:22:10,648
Idiot.

280
00:22:12,709 --> 00:22:16,111
When I saw how you fought, I was
prepared for us both to kill each other.

281
00:22:16,631 --> 00:22:19,133
But your attacks don't have
any weight behind them.

282
00:22:20,473 --> 00:22:22,174
Lightning Strike!

283
00:22:35,224 --> 00:22:36,384
Linie!

284
00:22:36,824 --> 00:22:37,585
Shit.

285
00:22:37,625 --> 00:22:42,247
Solltrag.

286
00:22:43,787 --> 00:22:46,749
Magic designed to kill demons.

